Director – Procurement
Morgan McKinley
UAE
Posted on: 1 May 2014
THE ROLE
Expand all
Our client is a leader in its field and recognised regionally and globally for its professional standards. Due to restructuring they are seeking a Director of Procurement who will be
responsible for the delivery of value through advanced sourcing methods; market knowledge and by obtaining best pricing, quality and service.
The Director will bring leadership and professional expertise in contract management, procurement and supply management in support for strategic goals and objectives. This includes identifying strategic sourcing initiatives that will reduce and rationalize spend, negotiating, developing and implementing procurement strategies, managing and executing contracts, developing an effective and professional procurement team and strengthening vendor relations.
Develop, implement and drive the best procurement process
Performs the accurate, timely, and cost-effective identification, sourcing, buying, warehousing, and delivery of material and services
Installing discipline & monitoring procurement controls to ensure compliance with the established policies with particular emphasis on quality and timely delivery
Manage the issuing and execution of contracts with vendors and ensure their fairness and the required level of contractual protection
Identify risks, opportunities and alternatives from the supply chain to provide added value
Provide an ethical and consistent approach to the procurement of goods and services
Administer, perform, and optimize the sourcing and competitive tenders (RFP/RFQ) in all spend categories
Produce tender lists for approval including appraisal of vendor capabilities, Financials, Capacity, Licenses, etc.
Drive through improvements that make best use of information systems, encouraging their use to share knowledge/ best practice/ experiences
Proactively manage & monitor the supply chain's performance
REQUIREMENTS
Essential:
Senior Procurement management experience; preferably with transport and facilities experience
Bachelors Degree required, MBA
Membership the Certified Institute of Purchasing and Supply (CIPS)
Arabic speaker
Skills:
•Solid experience in negotiating contractual terms and conditions
•Knowledge and application of best practice procurement techniques
•Demonstrated experience in drafting, negotiating, executing, and managing contracts / service agreements
•Experience preparing specifications and analyzing bids
•Demonstrated experience in vendor management
•Superior written and oral communication skills
ABOUT THE COMPANY
In November 2010, GCC specialist recruiter, iQ selection came together with global professional recruitment consultancy Morgan McKinley, under the name Morgan McKinley.
With 24 offices globally, Morgan McKinley connects specialist talent with leading employers across multiple industries and disciplines. We work very closely with international corporates, top investment banks and local SMEs to provide those looking for their next career move with the best job opportunities.
From our Dubai office, we provide specialist recruitment expertise spanning Financial Services & Finance; Sales, Marketing & Support; and Technical sectors throughout the GCC region, with dedicated consultants delivering focused sector and local knowledge. In addition, we are fully committed to promoting the government’s Emiratisation policy.
